<p>About a mile down the canal from where we were camped is the place where the Turks tried to cross the Canal, there is a big graveyard just close to it where they are all buried. Since the British have been down there they have built a lot of roads, running out to the firing line a distance of about 12 miles all the stores &amp; metal have to be brought here by barges &amp; the Gyppos do the labouring part of the contract they have all the up to date appliances here for road building, I don't think much of the Turks chance of ever breaking the British on the Canal if they ever try it on it will be the end of them, their idea is to</p>
